    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Expanding Investment Opportunities Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Securities and Exchange Commission to revise registration rules to allow a closed-end company to use offering and proxy rules currently available to other issuers of securities, thereby reducing filing requirements and restrictions on communications with investors in certain circumstances. (A closed-end company is a publicly traded investment management company that sells a limited number of shares to investors in an initial public offering.)</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2017-11-07</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-01-17T16:27:24Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2017-11-07T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <versionCode>17</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Expanding Investment Opportunities Act</b></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill directs the Securities and Exchange Commission to revise registration rules to allow a closed-end company to use offering and proxy rules currently available to other issuers of securities, thereby reducing filing requirements and restrictions on communications with investors in certain circumstances. (A closed-end company is a publicly traded investment management company that sells a limited number of shares to investors in an initial public offering.)</p>]]></text>
